articles.author: Nisha Anand
articles.title: World's first case of live parasitic worm found in Australian woman's brain - Hindustan Times
articles.description: Researchers believe that the woman contracted the infection while gathering edible shrubs near her residence in Australia's New South Wales. | World News
articles.content:
In the world's first case, an eight cm live worm was pulled out from the brain of a 64-year-old Australian woman during a surgery, the doctors said.
